The piece ends, and the conductor swivels around to accept the audience's applause. After a short bow, they extend their hand towards the left. At the signal, a second person comes out from behind the stage: the soloist, but something's off...
[[Next->PreStory6i]]

{}
In his left hand is a violin, its polished surface gleaming under the stage lights; in his right hand, a bow, extending towards the stage floor. You instictively flip through the program to find this soloist's name.
[[Next->PreStory8]]

{}
"Leo V."
[[Next->PreStory9]]

{}
The conductor has already turned around and, with a flick of their baton, the orchestra is brought back to life. Section by section, the hall fills with the vibrant notes of a carefully crafted symphony.
[[Next->PreStory10]]

{}
The soloist stands patiently to the side, eyes closed and deeply absorbed in the music. You find yourself being drawn into the lull of the accompaniment, until suddenly-
[[Next->PreStory11]]

{}
The soloist springs to life and the violin's first note pierces the air. This sudden note is held for what feels like an eternity, almost as if the violin is teasing the entire audience of a resolution that will never happen.
[[Next->PreStory12]]

{}
Eventually, the note is resolved, and you can feel the entire hall releasing a collectively held breath. The relief, however, did not last long; immediately, the violin transitions to a series of fiesty arpeggios, each one skillfully executed. 
[[Next->PreStory13]]

{}
The entire performance captivates your attention from beginning to end. You watched as the soloist's fingers appeared to dance over the strings, his bow gliding through all the spiccato sections.
[[Next->PreStory14]]

{}
Alas, the show must end eventually, and as the final note rang through the hall, the trance was finally broken. You suddenly realized you were sitting on the edge of your seat, and nearly tripped in getting up for the standing ovation.
[[Next->PreStory15]]

{}
As the audience cheered at the wonderous performance, each section of the orchestra accepts their praise with a humble bow. The conductor faces the audience with a grin, then gestures towards the amazing soloist.
[[Next->PreStory16]]

{}
You find yourself cheering with a newfound passion. Perhaps, this foreshadows a fateful encounter yet to come...
[[Next->Story1]]

